AuditDetail:
There is a List of Material and Service Providers R ABA 003 10 Version 16 dated 10/10/17 , but the company they use for labor services is not included.
//
No se incluyen el listado de proveedores aprobados la empresa que proveen servicios de mano de obra.

During the audit, there is a bin of expired chlorine stored in the outside.
//
Durante la auditoria se observa bin de cloro vencido almacenado en el patio.

The HACCP plan identifies an allergen identification control, however, it is controlled as operational control and not as CCP.
//
El plan HACCP identifica un Control de identificacion de alergenos, sin embrago se controla como control operativo y no como PCC.

During the visit to the plant, the wall floor junctions in poor condition are observed in the tunnel exit area.
//
Durante la visita a la planta se observa en el Area de salida de tunel las uniones pared piso en mal estado.

Verification of internal thermometers is done every 15 days and not daily as indicated in the clause.
//
La Verificacion de termometros interna se realiza cada 15 dias y no diariamente como lo indica la clausula.

A traceability exercise was carried out during the audit, however it is not possible to collect the documentation within 4 hours.
//
Se realizÃ³ ejercicio de trazabilidad durante la auditoria, sin embargo no se logra reunir la docmentacion dentro de las 4 horas.

However, the frequency of at least every 6 months was not followed, the last product verification test was performed as details below; 
Analysis reports were reviewed during the audit. 
Cook Shrimp;
test report from SGS no. #3801990 (19 October 2017) and #3809030 (14 February 2018)
Raw Shrimp;
test report from SGS no. #3801991 (19 October 2017) and #3809031 (14 February 2018)
Breaded shrimp;
test report from SGS no. #3801988 (19 October 2017) and #3809029 (14 February 2018) The facility conducted Microbiological Testing performed on Composite Samples of Each Primary Product Form and Aquaculture Drug testing performed by the external accredited laboratory (SGS (Thailand) Limited). Analysis report were reviewed during the audit. The facility test aquaculture drugs but excluded "Gentian violet and Leucogentian violet and Sulfonamide"
